---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words Ending in -IST — CYCLIST, TYPIST, FLORIST" description="Top -IST ending Scrabble words: CYCLIST (14pts), TYPIST (11pts), FLORIST (10pts). Master the person-suffix strategy for consistent scoring." keywords="scrabble ist words, cyclist scrabble, typist scrabble, florist scrabble, ist suffix strategy, person suffix scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words Ending in -IST — CYCLIST, TYPIST, FLORIST","description":"Master -IST suffix words in Scrabble: CYCLIST (14pts), TYPIST (11pts), FLORIST (10pts). The person-suffix strategy for consistent scoring.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ist"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the best -IST words for Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"CYCLIST scores 14 points with C(3)+Y(4)+C(3) providing strong consonant value. TYPIST delivers 11 points from Y(4)+P(3). FLORIST scores 10 with F(4) leading. The -IST ending uses common tiles (I+S+T = 3pts) to extend high-value bases."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does -IST suffix strategy work in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The -IST suffix turns verbs and nouns into person-words: CYCLE→CYCLIST, TYPE→TYPIST, FLORAL→FLORIST. It adds 3 tiles to existing bases, often creating 6-7 letter words. Many -IST words also take -S for plurals, giving you flexible back hooks."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can -IST words become bingos?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes — 7-letter -IST words qualify for bingo. CYCLIST (7 letters), FLORIST (7 letters), and CHEMIST (7 letters) all earn the 50-point bonus. Even without bingo, -IST words score well because bases often contain Y, C, or P tiles worth 3-4 points each."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Strategy</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending in -IST — Person-Suffix Strategy</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">-IST turns actions into people — and points into wins. CYCLIST packs 14 points into 7 letters with two C tiles (3 each) and a Y (4). TYPIST delivers 11 from just 6 tiles thanks to Y(4) and P(3). FLORIST scores a clean 10 at bingo length. The suffix costs only 3 points (I+S+T) but regularly creates 6-7 letter words that hit premium squares.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top Score (CYCLIST)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Suffix Tiles (IST)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">80+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid -IST Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Suffix Cost (I+S+T)</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top -IST Suffix Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 CYCLIST</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 points · 7 letters · C(3)+Y(4)+C(3)+L(1)+I(1)+S(1)+T(1) · Bingo eligible</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 TYPIST</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 points · 6 letters · T(1)+Y(4)+P(3)+I(1)+S(1)+T(1) · Compact scorer</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ FLORIST</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 points · 7 letters · F(4)+L(1)+O(1)+R(1)+I(1)+S(1)+T(1) · Bingo eligible</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ CHEMIST</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 points · 7 letters · C(3)+H(4)+E(1)+M(3)+I(1)+S(1)+T(1) · H+C+M power</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">-IST Suffix Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Back hook existing words:</span> If CYCLE, TYPE, or FLORA is on the board, adding -IST at the end creates a full word. You invest 3 cheap tiles to claim the entire word's score plus bonus letters.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bingo-length sweet spot:</span> Many -IST words hit exactly 7 letters — CYCLIST, FLORIST, CHEMIST, BASSIST. These earn the 50-point bingo bonus. Hold I+S+T when you have a strong 4-letter base.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Pluralise with -S:</span> Every -IST word takes -S (CYCLISTS, TYPISTS, FLORISTS). This gives you flexibility — play -IST now, or hold for -ISTS if an extra S appears.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CYCLIST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TYPIST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FLORIST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CHEMIST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">-IST is the <span class="text-white font-medium">most consistent bingo suffix for mid-range scores</span>. It pairs with bases containing C, Y, H, P, or F — tiles worth 3-4 points each. The 7-letter sweet spot means bingo bonus without needing rare tiles.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-with-ist/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Ending With -IST</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ize/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -IZE</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/common-bingo-endings/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Common Bingo Endings</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all -IST words from your tiles — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
